-> installer la camera
	-> installer le module usb_cam
		-> cd catkin_ws/src
		-> git clone https://www.github.com/ros-drivers/usb_cam.git
		-> cd .. 
		-> catkin_make
	-> installer le module image_view
		->sudo pat-get install ros-kinetic-image-view
		->sudo apt-get install v4l-utils
	-> installer camera-calibration
		-> sudo apt-get install ros-kinetic-camera-calibration
	-> installer track-alvar 
		-> sudo apt-get install ros-kinetic-ar-track-alvar

-> calibrer la camera
	-> cd catkin_ws/src
	-> rosrun camera_calibration cameracalibrator.py --size 8x6 --square 0.108 image:=/usb_cam/image camera:=/usb_cam
	-> suivre les instructions



-> installer arduino 
	-> installer arduino
		-> sudo apt-get install arduino
		-> lancer arduino
	-> installer rosserial 
		-> sudo apt-get install ros-kinetic-rosserial ros-kinetic-rosserial-arduino ros-kinetic-rosserial-xbee
		-> cd catkin_ws/src https://github.com/ros-drivers/rosserial.git
		-> cd ..
		-> catkin_make
		-> cd ~/sketchbook/librairies
		-> rm -rf ros_lib
		-> rosrun rosserial_arduino make_librairies.py
	-> connexion liaison serial 
		-> rosrun rosserial_python serial_node.py /dev/ttyACM0


-> installation du xbee
	-> branchez 
	-> ouvrir arduino
	-> Ctrl + shift + m 
	-> regler sur 57600 baud
	-> no line ending -> +++ (appuyer sur send pas ENTER)
		-> carriage return -> ATID - ATSH - ATSL - ATDH - ATDL
		-> refaire +++ is le tps est ecoulÃ© (rapidement)



ATID -> 11
ATSH -> 13A200
ATSL -> 408C5916
ATDH -> 13A200
ATDL -> 40C36490

